      "title": "Tech Lead / CTO Candidate (Full-stack)",
      "company": "Artytech",
      "url": "https://japan-dev.com/jobs/artytech/artytech-tech-lead--cto-candidate-full-stack-25pe6i",
      "location": "Tokyo, Tokyo, JP",
      "description": "■ About Artytech\n\r\n We are a small, fast-growing web production and digital marketing company based in Tokyo.\n\r\n We build and operate:\n\r\n \r\n Customer management systems\n\r\n Large-scale CMS platforms\n\r\n Marketing websites and landing pages\n\r\n \r\n We are a lean team, so each engineer has a direct impact on both the product and the business.\n\r\n If you enjoy building things from scratch, working autonomously, and being part of a team where your voice matters, you will feel right at home here.\n\n\r\n ■ Why This Role\n\r\n As we scale our business, we are looking for a technical leader who can help build a strong engineering foundation.\n\r\n This is not just an implementation role.\n\r\n You will:\n\r\n \r\n Define how we design and build systems\n\r\n Make key technical decisions\n\r\n Work closely with the business side\n\r\n Help shape the future engineering team\n\r\n \r\n If you are looking for a role where you can grow into a CTO-level position, this is a rare opportunity.\n\n\r\n ■ Responsibilities\n\r\n \r\n Design and develop web systems such as CRM and large-scale CMS\n\r\n Lead system architecture and technology decisions\n\r\n Estimate development effort and manage risks\n\r\n Implement high-quality frontend with strong design fidelity\n\r\n Build marketing websites and landing pages\n\r\n Review code and support other engineers (including external partners)\n\r\n Collaborate with business stakeholders\n\n\r\n \r\n ■ Requirements (Must)\n\r\n \r\n 3+ years of backend development experience\n\r\n Experience building web applications (CMS, CRM, or similar systems)\n\r\n Experience in system design, requirement definition, and estimation\n\r\n Solid understanding of frontend (HTML, CSS, JavaScript)\n\r\n Experience working in a team environment\n\r\n Ability to work in ambiguous and fast-changing environments\n\n\r\n \r\n ■ Preferred (Nice to have)\n\r\n \r\n Experience with Vue.js or React\n\r\n Experience leading projects or mentoring engineers\n\r\n Experience with AWS or other cloud platforms\n\r\n Experience working in startups or small teams\n\r\n Interest in business impact, not just technology\n\r\n Experience in client-facing development, such as agency, consulting, or outsourced development projects\n\n\r\n \r\n ■ Tech Stack\n\r\n Frontend\n\r\n \r\n HTML, CSS, JavaScript\n\r\n Vue.js, shadcn/ui, Lucide\n\r\n \r\n Backend\n\r\n \r\n Node.js, GraphQL\n\r\n AWS Lambda, AWS Amplify\n\r\n \r\n ※ Tech stack may vary depending on the project\n\n\r\n ■ Language\n\r\n \r\n Japanese: Not required\n\r\n English: Business level\n\r\n \r\n We have team members who mainly speak Japanese, so we value:\n\r\n \r\n Willingness to communicate across language differences\n\r\n A collaborative and proactive attitude\n\n\r\n \r\n ■ Working Conditions\n\r\n \r\n Location: Tokyo\n\r\n Employment: Full-time\n\r\n Visa sponsorship: Available (if applicable)\n\n\r\n \r\n ■ Who We&rsquo;re Looking For\n\r\n \r\n Someone who takes ownership even when things are not clearly defined\n\r\n Someone who balances technical quality with speed\n\r\n Someone who enjoys building systems in a growing company\n\r\n Someone who communicates openly and works well in a team\n\n\r\n \r\n ■ Why Join Us\n\r\n \r\n Opportunity to grow into a CTO-level role\n\r\n High ownership and autonomy\n\r\n Direct impact on company growth\n\r\n Close collaboration with business and clients",
