      "source": "Gogolook",
      "sourceType": "json-ld",
      "title": "US Market Intern (ScamAdviser)",
      "company": "Gogolook",
      "url": "https://jobs.lever.co/Gogolook/903b657d-9530-4f59-9dea-e9075163f3e6",
      "location": "Taipei",
      "description": "About us\n\n Gogolook is a leading TrustTech company founded in 2012 and listed on the Taiwan Stock Exchange in 2025 under the stock code 6902. With \"Build for Trust\" as its core value, the company has expanded its business from Asia to Europe and America. Gogolook’s AI technology is built on the world's largest database of digital scam data, encompassing phone numbers, websites, virtual currency wallet addresses, and other factors.\n\n The company provides diverse anti-scam and fintech services for both consumers and businesses. Its anti-scam offerings include the digital anti-scam app \"Whoscall\" and a range of enterprise scam prevention solutions in combination with \"ScamAdviser.\"\n\n The Fintech BU empowers consumers through data-driven financial services and inclusive lending: Roo.Cash（袋鼠金融）offers transparent matchmaking for financial products like credit cards, while JUJI（招財麻吉）provides an innovative microloan service for rapid, convenient funding during urgent financial needs.\n\n A foundation member of the Global Anti-Scam Alliance (GASA), Gogolook has also teamed up with a number of institutes such as the Taiwan National Police Agency Criminal Investigation Bureau, the Financial Supervisory Service of South Korea, Thai Royal Police, the Fukuoka city and Shibuya City government, the Philippines Cybercrime Investigation and Coordinating Center, and the Royal Malaysia Police and state government to fight scam, dedicated to creating a \"scam-free environment.\"\n\n Why you should join Gogolook\n\n Influential products: What we make are meaningful products that create values for society and defend against frauds.\n\n Emphasize self-growth: We encourage technical community activities, subsidize tickets for conferences and workshops so that learning is continuously supported by the company.\n\n Unleash your talent: We respect the professional opinions of everyone, encourage team members to discuss with each other, and make awesome products together.\n\n Transparent culture: We publicly share the company's information to all, every member can read and feedback, and become a part of participating in the proposal.\n\n ScamAdviser is seeking a highly motivated US Market Intern (hybrid/remote) to assist in our expansion into the North American market. This position offers the opportunity to participate in core business operations and contribute significantly to Gogolook’s global growth. The successful candidate will work alongside our global team to explore innovative anti-scam technologies and uphold our mission of protecting consumers worldwide.\n We especially welcome candidates with native-level English and strong understanding of U.S. online culture and consumer behavior.\n 1. Minimum availability of 20 hours per week, across at least 3 days.\n 2. Native or near-native English speakers with strong familiarity with the U.S. market are preferred. Taiwan-based candidates can work in a hybrid setup in Taipei. Exceptional candidates based in the U.S. may be considered for a fully remote arrangement (hourly rate: USD 7).\n 3. Able to commit to the role for at least one year.\n\\n\n\n Key Responsibilities: Market Intelligence: Conduct in-depth research on the US market, tracking local trends and competitive landscapes to define target user personas.\n GTM Strategy: Assist in the research and planning of Go-to-Market strategies for our US expansion.\n Campaign Execution: Assist in planning and executing multi-channel marketing campaigns, including tracking performance data to optimize results.\n Content Creation: Design and produce engaging social media content for the US audience, including graphics, short-form videos (Reels/TikTok), email newsletters, and one-pagers.\n Localization & Education: Create localized product tutorials and promotional materials to educate US users about our services.\n Agile Support: Assist with ad-hoc projects and tasks assigned by supervisors.\n\n What You’ll Gain: Mentorship from Experts: Receive direct guidance and mentorship from experienced leaders in the tech and marketing industry.\n Real Impact: Enjoy a high degree of autonomy and creative freedom—your ideas will directly shape our US market presence.\n Strategic Experience: Gain rare, hands-on experience participating in US Go-to-Market (GTM) strategy formulation and execution.\n Global Mindset: Fast-track your understanding of overseas marketing dynamics and cross-cultural communication.\n\n Requirements: Major in Marketing, Business, Communications, or other related fields.\n Highly proficient in English, with excellent written and verbal communication skills. Native English speaker is highly preferred.\n Proficient in document and presentation creation; ability to quickly master online tools such as Google Workspace, Google Analytics 4 (GA4), Canva, Mailchimp, and various AI tools.\n A strong interest in overseas markets and a willingness to embrace challenges during the internship.\n Proactive, detail-oriented, and capable of communicating clearly. Must be able to multitask effectively in a fast-paced environment.\n Fast learner capable of working independently under guidance.\n\n Nice to Have Prior working experience in the software industry.\n Basic understanding of B2C marketing and a strong passion for the tech industry, specifically App marketing.\n Familiarity with the North American internet trends and social media culture.\n\n\\n NT$210 - NT$210 an hour\n\\n Join Gogolook and become part of our global growth team, exploring innovative fraud prevention technologies and protecting consumer safety. We look forward to your contribution to advancing our mission and vision!",
