      "source": "Intel Workday Taiwan",
      "sourceType": "adapter:workday",
      "title": "Network Systems and Solutions Engineer - Intern",
      "company": "Intel Workday Taiwan",
      "url": "https://intel.wd1.myworkdayjobs.com/External/job/Taiwan-Taipei/Network-Systems-and-Solutions-Engineer---Intern_JR0282402",
      "location": "Taiwan, Taipei",
      "description": "Job Details:\n\n Job Description: \nThe Role and Impact\nJoin Intel as a System Software Engineering Undergraduate Intern and embark on an exciting journey to shape the future of technology. In this role, you will contribute to the design, development, and validation of system software across multiple layers of the software stack, including firmware, drivers, operating systems, and middleware. Your work will enable Intel platforms and technologies to perform at their best, driving innovation and excellence in the industry.\n\nAs an intern, you will have the opportunity to engage in cross-stack software optimization and contribute to reference platform development for specific domains and market segments. Through hands-on experience and collaborative projects, you will build foundational skills, apply knowledge, and explore future career opportunities while contributing to Intel's business goals.\n\nThis internship program is crafted to inspire growth, foster continuous learning, and provide meaningful support for your journey to becoming a top-tier software engineer.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n- Assist in the design, development, and validation of system software, including firmware, drivers, and middleware.\n- Participate in cross-stack software optimization efforts for enhanced performance across Intel platforms.\n- Support reference platform development targeted at specific domains and market segments.\n- Conduct code reviews to uphold software quality and standards.\n- Debug and troubleshoot issues in various layers of the software stack.\n- Apply problem-solving skills to address technical challenges and propose innovative solutions.\n- Utilize scripting, programming languages, and software development lifecycle practices to deliver high-quality results.\n- Collaborate with cross-functional teams in a dynamic and supportive environment.\n\n Qualifications:\n Minimum Qualifications\n- Student majors in Computer Science or Computer Engineering or Electrical Engineering or Electronic Engineer or the equivalent\n- Proficiency in programming languages such as C, C++, Python, or Java.\n- Familiarity with scripting languages and tools.\n- Basic understanding of operating system architecture and internals.\n- Demonstrated ability to debug and troubleshoot software issues.\n- Knowledge of software development lifecycle processes and methodologies.\n- Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.\n - ​1-year internship: full-time (40 hrs/week) Jul - Aug 2026; part-time (min. 24 hrs/week, 3 days on-site) Sep 2026 - Jun 2027\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n- Previous exposure to code review practices.\n- Practical exercising on Machine learning, AI tool & application, GenAI/LLM.\n- A passion for continuous learning and improvement in software engineering.\n- Ability to work effectively in a team-oriented, collaborative environment.\n- Interest in exploring innovative solutions and technologies in system software development.\n\nTake this opportunity to grow your skills, gain hands-on experience, and contribute to game-changing solutions at Intel. Apply today and become part of a team that is transforming the future of technology.\n\n           \n\n Job Type:\nStudent / Intern\n\n Shift:\nShift 1 (Taiwan)\n\n Primary Location: \nTaiwan, Taipei\n\n Additional Locations:\n\n Business group:\nThe Central Engineering Group (CEG) is Intel's data-driven organization that builds scalable engineering solutions across three pillars: Product Enablement (IP, tools, and methodologies), Custom ASIC (leveraging existing IP for custom silicon), and Foundry Enablement (supporting top customers and validating technologies). The team focuses on customer-driven, end-to-end solutions with short development cycles to deliver measurable business impact across Intel's product and foundry businesses.\n\n Posting Statement:\nAll qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, religious creed, sex, national origin, ancestry, age, physical or mental disability, medical condition, genetic information, military and veteran status, marital status, pregnancy, gender, gender expression, gender identity, sexual orientation, or any other characteristic protected by local law, regulation, or ordinance.\n Position of Trust\nN/A\n Work Model for this Role\nThis role will be eligible for our hybrid work model which allows employees to split their time between working on-site at their assigned Intel site and off-site. * Job posting details (such as work model, location or time type) are subject to change.\n *\n\nADDITIONAL INFORMATION: Intel is committed to Responsible Business Alliance (RBA) compliance and ethical hiring practices. We do not charge any fees during our hiring process. Candidates should never be required to pay recruitment fees, medical examination fees, or any other charges as a condition of employment. If you are asked to pay any fees during our hiring process, please report this immediately to your recruiter.\n\nTime type: Full time\n\nJob requisition id: JR0282402",
