      "source": "Logitech Workday Taiwan",
      "sourceType": "adapter:workday",
      "title": "Sr. Mechancial Design Engineer",
      "company": "Logitech Workday Taiwan",
      "url": "https://logitech.wd5.myworkdayjobs.com/Logitech/job/Hsinchu-Taiwan/Sr-Mechancial-Design-Engineer-Controller_145096",
      "location": "Hsinchu, Taiwan",
      "description": "Logitech is the Sweet Spot for people who want their actions to have a positive global impact while having the flexibility to do it in their own way.\n\n The Team and Role:\n\n The Logitech G team seek an individual passionate about gaming, who thrives in a collaborative environment, eager to take on pivotal roles in innovation and product development for the next generation of gaming controller products. A creative thinker with a passion for innovation to push the boundaries, along with the expertise to transform from idea to concept to product.  The ideal candidate has an active interest in the console & PC controller gaming category. \n\n Our Gaming Engineering team spreads worldwide, both in Asia and Europe, and focuses on the design of gaming peripherals including keyboards, mice, driving wheels, flight controllers and more. Our motivation is to help all gamers have the best in-game experience by focusing on user needs: big and small, young and less young, for all genders, because playing is such an important part of life.\n\n As a Senior Mechanical Design Engineer,  you are responsible for;\n Driving new product development & innovation activities.  \n\n Identifying and exploring new product concepts/features/user experiences for the controller gaming category\n\n Playing a leading role in a cross-functional team to design and develop these from product front end to successful mass production in the far east\n\n As a key member of the Logitech gaming team, the candidate is responsible for combining engineering expertise, testing and a relentless pursuit of creating the best products and experiences that are sold around the world. \n \n The ability to do 3D molding and apply scientific approaches & analysis tools to create robust mechanical designs for volume mass production is required. Additional responsibilities include ensuring product features achieve cost, schedule, reliability, regulatory, and safety goals.\n\n Your Contributions:\n\n Be Yourself. Be Open. Stay Hungry and Humble. Collaborate. Challenge. Decide and just Do. Share our passion for Equality and the Environment. These are the behaviours and values you’ll need for success at Logitech. In this role you will:\n\n As a key member of the Gaming ME team, you will be responsible for ideating, exploring  & prototyping mechanical & electromechanical solution concepts that transform user experiences. Along with delivering mechanical product designs for gaming products, from the Product Front End through product development and into successful mass production.\n You will also contribute to innovation and technology programs to enable gaming product evolution.\n\n Job description:\n Development of user centric gaming products (PC & Console Controllers) and participate in the development of User Experience (UX) research to develop customer focussed products\n\n Develop product architectures and new technology concepts\n\n Work with Industrial Designers, and product development teams to define and develop products from concept to Mass Production\n\n Lead & support innovation activities in the gaming controller product category an d continuous improvement/advancement of Engineering capabilities\n\n Build mechanical/electro-mechanical proof of concepts to evaluate UX, function, manufacturability, and/or robustness\n\n Ensure high quality robust design of complex mechanical systems and components using tools such as dFMEA, QFD and FEA simulation\n\n Analyse data generated from pilot builds and lab experiments\n\n Perform tolerance analyses to verify performance of mechanisms and cosmetic specifications in the presence of high volume dimensional variation\n\n Detailed 3D design and 2D documentation of all parts and assemblies\n\n Interacting with vendors as well as internal Manufacturing, Supply Chain, NPI and Supplier Quality Engineering groups to develop manufacturing processes & tooling\n\n Define reliability testing requirements and equipment\n\n Strong knowledge and experience in rapid prototyping, functional lab testing of concepts and analysis of test data\n\n Optimise designs for performance, quality and cost\n\n Key Qualifications:\n\n Education :\n Bachelor's  Degree in Mechanical/mechatronics/Electro - Mechanical Engineering (or similar)\n\n For consideration, you must bring the following minimum skills and experiences to our team:\n 5+ years experience in mechanical design/development of high volume consumer electronic products\n\n Detailed knowledge of plastics injection moulding and tooling, assembly process, cosmetic finishes & defect analysis\n\n Hard plastic, soft plastic, metal process\n\n Post treatment\n\n Fluent in Design/Development process and tools of high volume manufacturing\n\n Fluent in Pro/Engineer or similar 3D CAD package including Advanced Surfacing\n\n Strong knowledge in ANSYS simulation software\n\n Highly skilled in problem solving & risk management\n\n ‘Design Thinking’ mindset\n\n Strong Communication skills with experience in multicultural and multidisciplinary teams\n\n Experience of stakeholder management\n\n Proven ability of speaking up and taking ownership\n\n Self-motivated, able to work independently and as part of a team \n\n Strong Presentation skills\n\n Experience in working with and prototyping electro-mechanical solutions is a strong advantage\n\n Good command of English -  writing and speaking\n\n In addition, preferable skills and behaviours include...\n Communication skills in both Mandarin & English\n\n Keen interest in latest tech and gaming trends\n\n A passion for the gaming controller genre ( PC & Console)\n\n #LI-AL2/104\n\n Across Logitech we empower collaboration and foster play. We help teams collaborate/learn from anywhere, without compromising on productivity or continuity so it should be no surprise that most of our jobs are open to work from home from most locations. Our hybrid work model allows some employees to work remotely while others work on-premises. Within this structure, you may have teams or departments split between working remotely and working in-house.\n\nLogitech is an amazing place to work because it is full of authentic people who are inclusive by nature as well as by design. Being a global company, we value our diversity and celebrate all our differences. Don’t meet every single requirement? Not a problem. If you feel you are the right candidate for the opportunity, we strongly recommend that you apply. We want to meet you!\n\nWe offer comprehensive and competitive benefits packages and working environments that are designed to be flexible and help you to care for yourself and your loved ones, now and in the future. We believe that good health means more than getting medical care when you need it. Logitech supports a culture that encourages individuals to achieve good physical, financial, emotional, intellectual and social wellbeing so we all can create, achieve and enjoy more and support our families. We can’t wait to tell you more about them being that there are too many to list here and they vary based on location.\n\nAll qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, sex, age, color, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, protected veteran status, or on the basis of disability.\n\nIf you require an accommodation to complete any part of the application process, are limited in the ability, are unable to access or use this online application process and need an alternative method for applying, you may contact us toll free at +1-510-713-4866 for assistance and we will get back to you as soon as possible.\n\nTime type: Full time\n\nJob requisition id: 145096",
