      "url": "https://amat.wd1.myworkdayjobs.com/External/job/TainanTWN/XMLNAME-2025-Summer-Intern-Program----Process-Support-Engineer-------_R2611498",
      "location": "Tainan,TWN",
      "description": "Who We Are\n\n Applied Materials is a global leader in materials engineering solutions used to produce virtually every new chip and advanced display in the world. We design, build and service cutting-edge equipment that helps our customers manufacture display and semiconductor chips – the brains of devices we use every day. As the foundation of the global electronics industry, Applied enables the exciting technologies that literally connect our world – like AI and IoT. If you want to push the boundaries of materials science and engineering to create next generation technology, join us to deliver material innovation that changes the world. \n\n What We Offer\n\n Location:\nTainan,TWN\n You’ll benefit from a supportive work culture that encourages you to learn, develop, and grow your career as you take on challenges and drive innovative solutions for our customers. We empower our team to push the boundaries of what is possible—while learning every day in a supportive leading global company. Visit our Careers website to learn more. \n\n At Applied Materials, we care about the health and wellbeing of our employees. We’re committed to providing programs and support that encourage personal and professional growth and care for you at work, at home, or wherever you may go. Learn more about our benefits . \n\n 台灣應用材料暑期實習專案\n **申請資格：大學就學三年以上的在學學生（含碩、博士）；應屆畢業生即將進入職場者請勿投遞；若需繼續升學者請附上入學證明。\n **申請文件 : 提供中英文履歷; 中文自傳(同步提供英文版更加分); 學校成績單; 專業認證證照或作品集。\n **收件期間 : 2026/2/1 - 2026/4/15 (面試若符合資格，優先給予錄取通知)。\n **附加條件：\n 1. 實習期間：2026/7/1-2026/8/31。\n 2. 實習期間之交通與住宿需自理。\n 3. 實習期間，須全程參與，若無法承諾及配合，請勿投遞。\n 4. 實習尾聲，須提交報告，分享實習成果，方可領取結業證書。並正式納入公司人才庫。\n 5. 工作待遇：大學生月薪台幣42,000元，碩士生月薪台幣48,000元，博士生月薪台幣53,000元。\n\n Key Responsibilities\n 1. Experience in Applied Taiwan Semiconductor Product Group\n 2. Overview of Semiconductor Industry : Study worldwide semiconductor equipment companies and biggest semiconductor foundry company\n 3. Thin film experiments at Display R&D Lab 4. Semiconductor tool and parts studying at Taiwan Repaired Center and Equipment Product Group) Training\n\n Requirements\n Skill: Excellent (listening, speaking, reading and writing) in English. TOEIC > 750,\n Knowledge: Well-known semiconductor-related studying\n Experience: Semiconductor-related experiment at lab is preferred.\n Education (Major/Degree): Major in 3-year university or above, College of Engineering, Science, Electrical Engineering and Computer Science and Semiconductor.\n\n Additional Information\n\n Time Type:\nFull time\n Employee Type:\nIntern / Student\n Travel:\nNot Specified\n Relocation Eligible:\nNo\n\n Applied Materials is an Equal Opportunity Employer. Qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, national origin, citizenship, ancestry, religion, creed, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, veteran or military status, or any other basis prohibited by law.\n\nTime type: Full time\n\nJob requisition id: R2611498",
