      "url": "https://nvidia.wd5.myworkdayjobs.com/NVIDIAExternalCareerSite/job/Taiwan-Hsinchu/Manufacturing-Test-Engineer---Board_JR2017816",
      "location": "Taiwan, Hsinchu",
      "description": "We are looking for a self-motivated manufacturing test Engineer to be in TW Hsinchu. You will support to build next-generation NVIDIA board level Tesla PCIE products, work closely with cross functional teams to help bring highly complex board products from its design phase into mass production.\n\n The ideal candidate will drive the scope of test methodology on GPU, Tesla PCIE products with cross functional teams, review design concept, define validation plan, develop/automate config of test infrastructure to test various product features, optimize test manufacturability. Familiar with electronic products production build and test flow, have production test capacity sense and capability.\n\n What you will be doing:\n Work closely with NV internal team and CM factory to maintain test infrastructure factors & mfg flow implementation.\n\n Support the upcoming roadmap execution and fast ramping of test capacity/test infrastructure in line with fast growing of manufacturing volumes in multiple CM sites, Define and improve board manufacturing processes.\n\n Designs, develops, and implements cost-effective methods of testing and troubleshooting systems and equipment for all phases of board level product development and manufacturing.\n\n Support diagnosis and analyze test issues at the board level product with hardware, software, and operations engineering teams, Assist and provide feedback on board level product debug tools to SW team members.\n\n Board level product test setup/troubleshooting (NPI+MP) follow up if CM factory has any issues for Diag package and FTP document.\n\n Help design tools to automate product definitions, data collection, test case execution, and results analysis.\n\n What we need to see:\n BS or MS in EE, CS, Automatic Control, Systems Engineering.\n\n 5+ overall years’ experience with Manufacturing Test and test infrastructure develops experience. Familiar with GPU, DPU and data center tested platforms software.\n\n Deep knowledge of low-level software drivers and kernel.\n\n Ability to debug at board/system level and usage of probing hardware.\n\n Self-motivated and able to work effectively across different functional teams from local and oversea.\n\n Excellent written and oral communication skills in English, good communication and organization skills, with a logical approach to problem solving, good time management and task prioritization.\n\n Be proactive and drive projects with a minimum of supervision.\n\n Ways to stand out from the crowd:\n Knowledge of board and data center manufacturing process, system testing.\n\n Experience in x86 assembly and knowledge of the PC architecture and power management.\n\n Familiarity in Shell, JAVA, Perl, Python script programming  and muti kinds of OS, such as Windows, CentOS, Ubuntu.\n\n Experience in test solution, failure processing, and test program development\n\n Experience with running system level diagnostic tests and deeper understanding of the purpose of those tests\n\n With competitive salaries and a generous benefits package, NVIDIA is widely considered to be one of the most desirable employers in the world. We have some of the most brilliant and talented people in the world working for us. If you are creative, autonomous and love a challenge, we want to hear from you. We are an equal opportunity employer and value diversity at our company. We do not discriminate on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, or disability status.\n\nTime type: Full time\n\nJob requisition id: JR2017816",
