      "location": "Hsinchu, Taiwan",
      "description": "Logitech is the Sweet Spot for people who want their actions to have a positive global impact while having the flexibility to do it in their own way.\n\n The role and team:\nThe Senior Color Material and Finishing (CMF) Designer develops design concepts and specifications that optimize the function, ergonomics, perceived value and appearance of physical hardware products and systems for product consumers and end users. Responsible for creation and development of innovative and engaging products contributing from initial storytelling ‘vision’, through concept development.  You will have exposure to the full product development journey. You will partner with internal and external marketing and design groups to research and analyze design trends and customer feedback for incorporation into product enhancements, new product design and overall design language and strategy, validating product design specifications and production requirements with insourced and outsourced manufacturing and engineering groups. \n\n Your Contribution:\nBe Yourself. Be Open. Stay Hungry and Humble. Collaborate. Challenge. Decide and just Do. Share our passion for Equality and the Environment. These are the behaviors and values you’ll need for success at Logitech. In this role you will:\n Research consumer lifestyle and design trends, cross-referencing inspiration from fashion, beauty, furniture, automotive, and more.\n\n Build Color Material and Finishing (CMF) strategies that connect consumer lifestyle trends with material technologies and product concepts.\n\n Research innovative materials and processes to drive game-changing product innovation.\n\n Work closely with the Engineering Group to develop technologies into feasible ingredients for mass manufacture.\n\n Create Color Material and Finishing (CMF) specification documents to enable Engineers to realize the product concept.\n\n Ensure all product materials are color-matched, approved, and clearly documented.\n\n Build Pinterest boards, trade show reports, material sample libraries, and technical reference documents for the global Logitech Design community.\n\n Key Qualifications:\nFor consideration, you must bring the following minimum skills and experiences to our team:\n At least 5 years of professional Color Material and Finishing (CMF) design experience, defining trends, color, material, and finishes for mass manufacture.\n\n Excellent visualization and presentation skills, using Adobe Creative Suite and Keyshot.\n\n Technical expertise in manufacturing processes and a passion for emerging material technologies.\n\n Strong organizational skills.\n\n Great visual, verbal, and written communication skills.\n\n Fluent in English.\n\n Experience in Industrial Design or Mechanical Product Design Engineering.\n\n Well-versed in user-centered design methods and techniques.\n\n Strong portfolio of cutting-edge design demonstrating solid design skills and forward thinking.\n\n Understanding of the latest CE technologies and manufacturing processes.\n\n To be considered for this role, please ensure your updated portfolio is either attached in your resume or provided as a separate attachment during submission.\n\n #LI-SL1/104\n\n Across Logitech we empower collaboration and foster play. We help teams collaborate/learn from anywhere, without compromising on productivity or continuity so it should be no surprise that most of our jobs are open to work from home from most locations. Our hybrid work model allows some employees to work remotely while others work on-premises. Within this structure, you may have teams or departments split between working remotely and working in-house.\n\nLogitech is an amazing place to work because it is full of authentic people who are inclusive by nature as well as by design. Being a global company, we value our diversity and celebrate all our differences. Don’t meet every single requirement? Not a problem. If you feel you are the right candidate for the opportunity, we strongly recommend that you apply. We want to meet you!\n\nWe offer comprehensive and competitive benefits packages and working environments that are designed to be flexible and help you to care for yourself and your loved ones, now and in the future. We believe that good health means more than getting medical care when you need it. Logitech supports a culture that encourages individuals to achieve good physical, financial, emotional, intellectual and social wellbeing so we all can create, achieve and enjoy more and support our families. We can’t wait to tell you more about them being that there are too many to list here and they vary based on location.\n\nAll qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, sex, age, color, religion, sexual orientation, gender identity, national origin, protected veteran status, or on the basis of disability.\n\nIf you require an accommodation to complete any part of the application process, are limited in the ability, are unable to access or use this online application process and need an alternative method for applying, you may contact us toll free at +1-510-713-4866 for assistance and we will get back to you as soon as possible.\n\nTime type: Full time\n\nJob requisition id: 145766",
