      "source": "NVIDIA Workday",
      "sourceType": "adapter:workday",
      "title": "ICT Test Engineer",
      "company": "NVIDIA Workday",
      "url": "https://nvidia.wd5.myworkdayjobs.com/NVIDIAExternalCareerSite/job/Taiwan-Hsinchu/ICT-Test-Engineer_JR2017812",
      "location": "Taiwan, Hsinchu",
      "description": "We are looking for an ICT Test Engineer regular employee to be located in TW. This engineer is going to provide support for SXM, L6-DC, other board-level products and upcoming LPU/ENET products manufacturing builds, especially for ICT test related items. Report to OPS TSG team manager in SZ.\n\n What you will be doing:\n Provide support for board-level NPI and production builds.  \n\n Collaborate with production lines to analyze and resolve ICT test fixture anomalies.\n\n Maintenance ICT programs, analyze and address defects for and troubleshoot failures.\n\n Monitoring production ICT tests including tester fixture status, test yield, capacity and all fixtures GRR status.\n\n PCBA design DFT/DFM review and feedback.\n\n Support manufacturing validation process.\n\n Coordinate with NV TSG Shenzhen team, and Foxconn factory teams for supporting products.\n\n What we need to see:\n Degree in Electronics and Information or related fields.\n\n 5+ years of experience in ICT (In-Circuit Test) programming and fixture debugging skills.\n\n Knowledge of analog and digital circuits and has circuit analysis capabilities.\n\n Experience in PCBA power-on testing and understanding of Boundary Scan testing processes.\n\n Familiarity with electronic products manufacturing processes including SMT, PTH, ICT, assembly, functional test, etc.\n\n Familiarity with PCBA design DFT/DFM review and feedback.\n\n Good teamwork and communication skills, self-driven & motivated\n\n Hands-on experience with lab tools (oscilloscopes, multimeters)\n\n High work responsibilities, teamwork and good communication in English.\n\n Ways to stand out from the crowd:\n Have good mechanical sense or experience in test fixtures/jigs debugging or adjustment.\n\n Familiar with fixtures validation procedures, such as SG, DnP, GRR, etc.\n\nTime type: Full time\n\nJob requisition id: JR2017812",
