      "location": "JP",
      "description": "Contract Type: Contract (Quasi-agency)\n\nClient: Global Pharmaceutical Company\n\nPosition: Employee Substitute (Infrastructure PM/PMO Support)\n\nNumber of Positions: 2\n\nWork Style: Primarily Remote Work\n\n*Day trips to the office approximately once a week are possible\n\n*In-person intensive discussions, such as workshops, may occur.\n\nWorking Hours: 9:00 AM - 6:00 PM\n\nLanguage Requirements:\n\nJapanese: Native\n\nEnglish: Business Level (Recommended: TOEIC 800 or above)\n\n■ Position Summary\n\nYou will be responsible for supporting the PM/PMO team in driving global infrastructure projects at a global pharmaceutical company.\n\nIn this role, you will be responsible for ensuring the smooth implementation of global projects, coordinating with stakeholders, and assisting in identifying and resolving issues.\n\n■ Main Duties\n\n[Global Project PM/PMO Support]\n\nPM support for global projects\n\nPresenting requirements to vendors and interviewing current contractors\n\nSupporting the organization and resolution of internal issues\n\n(Example: Clarifying issues when Japan-specific settings and global standard settings do not match)\n\nSupporting the development of compromises and reaching consensus\n\n[Global System Deployment Support]\n\nPM support for global system deployment\n\nSupporting the creation of deployment plans\n\nSupporting collaboration with members from each region\n\nChecking deployment progress and addressing issues\n\n(Example: Identifying causes and solutions when deployment to some devices is not possible due to technical issues)\n\n[Incident/Inquiry Response]\n\nCompiling various incidents and inquiries\n\nPreparing incident/inquiry reports and sharing them with relevant parties\n\nVerifying content, considering response strategies, and issuing instructions to relevant members\n\n■ Required Skills and Experience\n\n[Project Management]\n\nProject management experience: 10+ years\n\nOf which, 5+ years of global project experience\n\n[Technical Skills]\n\nExperience in global integration and operations in the following areas:\n\nMicrosoft 365\n\nIntune\n\nEntra ID (Azure AD)\n\nWindows Client\n\nActive Directory\n\nBroad technical knowledge in infrastructure, cloud, and operations.\n\n[Documentation and Coordination Skills]\n\nDocumentation skills\n\nExperience proposing solutions to issues and monitoring their implementation status.\n\n[Language Skills]\n\nBusiness communication in English (meetings and report writing).\n\nTeam members are primarily Japanese.\n\nRelated departments are overseas (primarily the US and Europe).\n\nParticipation in international meetings.\n\n■ Desired Profile (Soft Skills)\n\nLogical thinking skills\n\nAbility to organize abstract requirements and translate them into concrete ones\n\nAbility to smoothly coordinate with stakeholders while working on the project.\n\n■ Preferred Qualifications\n\nProject management certifications such as PMP and PRINCE2.",
