      "description": "Client: Japanese-owned manufacturing company\n\nPosition: Infrastructure/Global Project PM/PMO\n\nWork Location: Tokyo Station area (office-based/100% in-office)\n\nStart Date: ASAP - Long-term\n\nNumber of Positions: 3-4\n\nContract Type: 3-month renewal\n\n■ Position Overview\n\nAs a senior project manager in the infrastructure/network area of the technology department, you will be responsible for planning, executing, and managing the progress of global projects.\n\nBased in Tokyo, you will drive projects from the user company's perspective, ensuring smooth progress and success.\n\n■ Main Duties\n\nProject planning and schedule management\n\nCommunication and coordination between related departments and teams\n\nProject progress management and reporting\n\nRisk management and problem-solving and proposal\n\nClient relationship building and requirements organization\n\nVendor management\n\n■ Desired Profile\n\nExtensive project management knowledge and experience\n\nPM or PL experience in the infrastructure/network field\n\nStrong communication skills\n\nProblem-solving and leadership skills\n\n■ Required Qualifications\n\nExperience driving projects from the user company's perspective\n\n(Expected role: Project lead)\n\n10+ years of work experience in the infrastructure field\n\nBusiness-level English proficiency\n\nAbility to be present in the office (100% presence)",
